  "text": "However, trained SVM model can be visualized using feature selection approach specified in [CITATION_1] . Keywords or features describing the user segments are the ones, whose weights in SVM normal vector contribute most when deciding if the centroid of the positive class is positive. Figure 3 shows top keywords describing the segment defined in Figure 2 . This information was found in practice to be useful to the web site editors and marketers to better understand the behavior of their users (e.g. what does a particular segment of users typically read).",
